The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, February 04, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Mumbai, Feb. 3: Sebi has asked Kosha Investments Ltd to make an open offer to shareholders of Snowcem India Ltd with June 29, 1999 as reference date to calculate price and also pay 15 per cent interest to shareholders thereon. The public announcement should be made within 45 days of passing of the order, Sebi said in a release. The acquirers should pay interest at 15 per cent per annum for the loss of interest caused to the shareholders from October 28, 1999 till the date of actual payment of consideration for shares accepted in the offer, it said.																								 Mumbai, Feb. 3: Sun Pharmaceutical has entered into an agreement with two large shareholders of its subsidiary, Caraco Pharmaceutical Lab, to acquire most of their common stock and options for $42 million. This will increase the companys and its affiliates equity positions in Caraco to over 60 per cent from 44 per cent.																								 Mumbai, Feb. 3: Cipla Ltd has approved the demerger of six private limited companies, who currently own the land and building of the firms Goa factory. Cipla would issue shares at par and allot equity shares of Rs 10 each to the shareholders of the demerged companies.																								 Mumbai, Feb. 3: The Reserve Bank has revised the exemption limit for declaration of export of goods and software to $25,000 as against the earlier limit of Rs 25,000 with effect from April 1, 2004.																								 Calcutta, Feb. 3: Normal operations has resumed at the state-owned Great Eastern Hotel following the withdrawal of the seizure notices by the Income Tax authorities on the hotels bank accounts.
